NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So with 10-11 and 5+ clubs and a 4-card major, you bid the major. However, with an opening hand, with 5+ clubs and a 4 card major, you can and should bid 2C. That way you then show your 4-card major at your 2nd bid. You have both established a game force and nicely described your hand. Therefore, 1D-P-2C does not deny a 4-card major.|
