NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In 2 over 1 the most popular treatment is to play 2C over 1D as a game force. However, I do not agree with that treatment. The reason being, you have a real bidding problem over 1D if you have 10-11 and clubsyou do not have forcing NT available. Over 1 of a major, you have the forcing NT to take care of the 10-11 club hand. I use the SAYC treatment, even playing 2 over 1, for the auction 1D-P-2C. That is, 2C only promises 10 points.|
